<h2>4 · Explain Your Lesson Code 🎥</h2>
<p>In today's live lesson you wrote your own flying-ship code. Now explain <strong>your own code</strong> in a short phone video. You may show it running on screen. Talk through it like you are teaching someone, and try to use these words: <strong>X axis</strong>, <strong>Y axis</strong>, <strong>key press</strong>, <strong>increase</strong>, <strong>speed</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your ship flying in all four directions as you press the keys.</li>
<li>Read your four <code>if keys[...]</code> lines out loud and say which way each one moves the ship.</li>
<li>Point at where <code>ship_x</code> and <code>ship_y</code> are used to draw the ship.</li>
<li>Say what <code>SPEED</code> does and what number you chose.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
